issue.title: Add mypy.ini and mypy error fixes
issue.body:
<!--
Thanks for contributing a pull request! Please ensure you have taken a look at
the contribution guidelines: https://github.com/microsoft/graspologic/CONTRIBUTING.md#how-to-create-an-actionable-bug-report
-->

#### Reference Issues/PRs
#504 

#### What does this implement/fix? Explain your changes.
- Add `mypi.ini` since the 3rd party packages dont have type checks. This stops errors due to imports.
- Two error fixes in mypy

The above will pass mypy check.

#### Any other comments?
- @dwaynepryce - the command for mypy check needs to add `--config-file ./mypi.ini`.
- I think the mypy check right now is kind of useless without some sort of coverage. Maybe something like `--disallow-untyped-defs` ([description](https://mypy.readthedocs.io/en/stable/command_line.html#cmdoption-mypy-disallow-untyped-defs)) arg to be included. This will fail the check unless all functions have type hints. Thoughts?

body: Added the good first issue label - if any newcomers are reading this, adding type hints to any functions/classes (doesn't have to be all of them!) would be much appreciated.
